item.title: CVE-2022-21948|2024-08-03T03:00:54.462Z -- opensuse -- paste
item.description: An Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting') vulnerability in paste allows remote attackers to place Javascript into SVG files. This issue affects: openSUSE paste paste version b57b9f87e303a3db9465776e657378e96845493b and prior versions.
